# Horizontal Scrolling Patterns

## Container Structure
Implement horizontal scrolling with proper indicators and smooth behavior:

```tsx
{/* Horizontal Scrollable Container */}
<div className="relative">
  <div className="overflow-x-auto pb-4 scroll-smooth">
    <div className="flex gap-6 min-w-max min-h-[600px] items-stretch py-2">
      {/* Scrollable content */}
    </div>
  </div>
  
  {/* Left Scroll Indicator only - NO right indicator */}
  <div className="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-background/90 to-transparent pointer-events-none" />
</div>
```

## Platform-Country Header Scrolling
Headers must be draggable and reorderable:

```tsx
<div className="overflow-x-auto pb-4 scroll-smooth">
  <DndContext collisionDetection={closestCenter} onDragEnd={handleDragEnd}>
    <SortableContext items={platformCountryGroups.map(g => g.platformCountry)} strategy={horizontalListSortingStrategy}>
      <div className="flex gap-4 min-w-max">
        {platformCountryGroups.map(({platformCountry, groups: platformGroups}) => (
          <SortableHeaderItem
            key={platformCountry}
            platformCountry={platformCountry}
            platform={platform}
            country={country}
            campaignCount={visiblePlatformGroups.length}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </SortableContext>
  </DndContext>
</div>
```

## Table Container Scrolling
Each platform-country group has its own horizontal scroll:

```tsx
{/* Section with scroll hint */}
<div className="bg-primary/5 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-primary">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
    <div>
      <h3 className="text-xl font-semibold">{platform} - {country}</h3>
      <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">{count} kampanya tablosu</p>
    </div>
    <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground bg-background/80 px-3 py-2 rounded-full border">
      ← → Kaydırarak görüntüle
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{/* Scrollable tables */}
<div className="relative">
  <div className="overflow-x-auto pb-4 scroll-smooth">
    <div className="flex gap-6 min-w-max min-h-[600px] items-stretch py-2">
      {/* Individual tables with fixed widths */}
      <div className="flex-shrink-0" style={{ width: `${dynamicWidth}px` }}>
        {/* Table content */}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Critical Rules
- ✅ Always use `scroll-smooth` for better UX
- ✅ Only show left gradient indicator, NEVER right
- ✅ Use `flex-shrink-0` to prevent content compression
- ✅ Include scroll hints in UI ("← → Kaydırarak görüntüle")
- ✅ Ensure `min-h-[600px] items-stretch` for equal table heights
- ✅ Use appropriate gap spacing (`gap-4` for headers, `gap-6` for tables)
- ❌ NO internal table scrolling - tables must expand width instead